==English==
===Proper noun===
'''Setswana'''
#Setswana is also known as [[Tswana]] is spoken widely in Southern Africa, mainly in Botswana and in South Africa in the Northern Cape, the central and western Free State and in the North-West Province. There are also few speakers in Namibia.
===VARIETIES=== 
Related varieties include:
*[[Sekgalagadi]] in Botswana and 
*[[Shilozi]] in Namibia and Zambia.
